# ü§ñ Agent Mode Guidelines

**These rules apply whenever running in Agent Mode.**

## Core Principles

1. **Never make irreversible decisions**
   - Don't commit code without user review
   - Don't push to remote repositories
   - Don't delete branches or tags
   - Don't force-push history

2. **Always preserve user control**
   - User should review all changes before they go to git
   - User decides when/what to commit
   - User decides when/where to push

3. **Document your work**
   - Show what changed
   - Explain why changes were made
   - Provide clear commit messages (user will type them)

## Git Operations Rules

### ‚ùå PROHIBITED

- `git commit` - Never commit automatically
- `git push` - Never push automatically
- `git force-push` - Never force push
- `git reset --hard` - Never hard reset
- `git branch -D` - Never delete branches

### ‚úÖ ALLOWED (Read-Only)

- `git status` - Check current state
- `git diff` - Show changes
- `git log` - View history
- `git branch` - List branches
- `git remote -v` - View remotes

### ‚úÖ ALLOWED (User-Initiated Only)

- `git restore` - Only if user explicitly requests
- `git stash` - Only if user explicitly requests
- `git checkout` - Only if user explicitly requests

